ion that X confers a real distribution and data-access advantage on Grok (large MAU base, native integration, proprietary real-time content stream, bidirectional ecosystem benefits). However, the **quantitative** figures carry material caveats: the 350M daily posts metric is contaminated by AI-generated content and Grok\'s own outputs, the 117M Grok-user figure is an estimate derived from server-request sourcing with acknowledged deduplication limits, and the company itself disclaims MAU stability as a strategic priority. An analyst should therefore treat the distribution advantage as **directionally supported but not precisely quantifiable** from the disclosed metrics, and should not infer durable competitive moats from a single point-in-time snapshot.\n\n---\n\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026) — definitions of MAU and daily posts, Grok/X integration disclosures, risk factors on AI usage fluctuations and data limitations"\n    }\n  ]\n}'
